16 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 54-03 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
17 and enacted as follows:
18 Voting on legislation - Immunity - Affirmative defense.
19 If an individual who is a member of the legislative assembly adheres to:
20 1. Legislative rules requiring an individual to disclose a personal or private interest to the
21 member's respective chamber of the legislative assembly, the president of the senate,
22 or the speaker of the house, the individual is immune from criminal prosecution under
23 the laws of this state for an offense arising from the individual voting on a measure in
24 the senate or house of representatives.
25 2. Informal advice from a staff member of the ethics commission , reliance on the advice
26 is an affirmative defense in a prosecution for an offense arising from the individual
27 voting on a measure in the senate or house of representatives.
